==Dammam Mosque bomb blast==
29 May, 2015 is the noteworthy Friday, being the last and the second consecutive Friday chosen by the ISIS to attack on Shia Mosques during Friday prayers. Reportedly four people were killed and dozens injured when a car exploded in the parking lot of the Imam Hussain Mosque situated in Dammam.  The news has already been included in the Current Events of May 29, 2015.

Presently there is no page to cover the details of above incident.  Therefore, I am creating a section in "2015 Qatif mosque bombing".  If contested or it is desired that a new page is necessary for Dammam Mosque Bomb Blast, then it can be done. [[User:Nannadeem|Nannadeem]] ([[User talk:Nannadeem|talk]]) 18:39, 29 May 2015 (UTC)

==Name change proposal==
In order the page title could cover the subject of both incidents of suicide bombs blasting within a week, one at Qatif Mosque and the second at Dammam Mosque, it is proposed that the title of page be changed as:

:: from  "2015 Qatif mosque bombing"  to  '''2015 Qatif and Dammam Mosques bombing'''. [[User:Nannadeem|Nannadeem]] ([[User talk:Nannadeem|talk]]) 12:43, 4 June 2015 (UTC)
:::'''Support''' linked attacks by ISIS on Shia mosques a week apart. &mdash;[[User:Jonny Nixon|<font color="blue">Jonny Nixon</font>]] - ([[User talk:Jonny Nixon|<small><font color="orange">Talk</font></small>]]) 01:43, 8 June 2015 (UTC)

::: Change of name is supported  <small class="autosigned">—&nbsp;Preceding [[Wikipedia:Signatures|unsigned]] comment added by [[Special:Contributions/119.159.220.188|119.159.220.188]] ([[User talk:119.159.220.188|talk]]) 10:52, 8 June 2015 (UTC)</small><!-- Template:Unsigned IP --> <!--Autosigned by SineBot-->

'''Cockmi Indian Reserve No. 3''', officially '''Cockmi 3''', is one of the three [[Indian reserve]]s of the [[Wuikinuxv Nation]] [[band government]] located on the west tip of [[Walbran Island]], which is near [[Darby Channel]]<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/64424.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Cockmi 3 (Indian reserve)"]</ref> in the area of [[Fitz Hugh Sound]] on the [[British Columbia Coast|Central Coast of British Columbia]], [[Canada]].  The other two Wuikinuxv reserves are Kiltala Indian Reserve No. 2 on the [[Kilbella River]] near [[Kilbella Bay]] and [[Katit Indian Reserve No. 1]], up the [[Wannock River]] from [[Rivers Inlet, British Columbia|the community of Rivers Inlet]] at the entrance to [[Owikeno Lake]].

