'''Amber Jones''' is the former leader of the [[Green Party of Saskatchewan]] serving in this office from 2008 until 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/saskatchewan/sask-green-party-leader-calls-for-caution-in-oil-patch-1.760637|title=Sask. Green party leader calls for caution in oil patch|publisher=CBC News|date=22 April 2008|accessdate=9 February 2016}}</ref><ref name="CC1">{{cite web|url=http://www.canada.com/story_print.html?id=42b711d7-15fc-47d5-b420-b4a09c799113|title=Children should be seen and heard|date=7 May 2008|publisher=Canada.com|accessdate=25 November 2015}}</ref><ref name="CCM2">{{cite web|url=http://www.canada.com/story.html?id=8a402243-b976-48fe-b9f9-0952f2b45994|title=Green Party appeal broad, leader says|date=23 October 2007|publisher=Canada.com|language=English|accessdate=25 November 2015}}</ref> Jones is a graduate of the [[University of Saskatchewan]]. She also unsuccessfully ran for the [[Green Party of Canada|federal Green party]] in the [[Canadian federal election, 2008|2008 federal election]] in the riding of [[Saskatoon—Rosetown—Biggar]]. She placed third out of seven candidates winning 1,228 votes losing to Conservative party nominee, [[Kelly Block]].

